                    <ul>
                        <li>Camp Dream Street is hosted by JCC on the Palisdaes in Tenafly, New Jersey.</li>
                        <br>
                        <li>The camp is available to oncology patients, and children with chronic hematological diseases such as sickle cell anemia and hemophilia.</li>
                        <br>
                        <li>It was founded in 1990, starting with only 20 campers.</li> 
                        <br>
                        <li>Now, 165 campers attend each summer, between the ages of 4 and 13.</li>
                        <br>
                        <li>All counselors at Camp Dream Street are volunteers and there are on-site oncology nurses on staff.</li>
                        <br>
                        <li>There are oncology nurses and social workers on staff as well.</li>
                    </ul>
